name: Valley View

reviews.review_text:
Food was really good, we had ordered kingfish thali, chonak thali, butter chicken, Paratha and lemon drinks.. the fish size was really big and tasty and worth the try.. i would give it 5/5 on food.. they also serve alcohol.

The only pain was their service, we had ordered 6 chonak and one kingfish thali and they prepared it vice versa.. the waiter came to ask of we were fine to have 5 kingfish thalis but when we denied he readily and politely agreed to rectify their mistake.. but very soon another waiter arrived with kingfish thalis and he had no clue.. so their internal communication was little off...we had ordered one lemon drink without sugar but even that was missed..

Overall food is awesome.. just waiters need to communicate internally better..

This place is close to the highway with lot of parking area. There are many steps to climb to the restaurant so it is little difficult for aged members. We visited this place on 1 June 2024 for lunch. We tried the Goan chonak and modso thali with vellyo rawa fry. The thali consisted of rice, prawn curry, bhindi bhaji, one piece of fish, kismoor, shevyo, sol kadi, salad, pickle and papad. I was disappointed with the salad served in the thali as it was all cut cabbage and one piece of carrot. However, the fried fish in the thali was fresh. The sweet in the thali was tasteless. The vellyo fry  was not that fresh but had a little better salad with some tomato and onion pieces. I found the thali a little expensive for the quality and quantity. The service was so slow that we had to wait for an hour till the food arrived. The staff is not welcoming at all.

Valley View Restaurant and Bar It is conveniently located across from the highway, where you will find the best seafood here.
People do come over to this place to have their various dishes,and it never disappoints them.
It is one of the best restaurants to visit in Goa and enjoy your various cuisines.
Goa is famous for its natural beauty, where people enjoy the weather anytime they come over to chill.
The restaurant has an amazing atmosphere with natural views just like the forest around it and cool vibes to enjoy together with friends and family. It tends to make you feel like having your meal with greenery all around you and also enjoy it while sharing your thoughts and love.
It has ample parking space as well for all vehicles.
The place is big enough to enjoy the natural view as they have an amazing ground beside the restaurant that makes it a little eye-catching to watch.
The restaurant has an outdoor seating area that is quiet and warm as well.
We tried out king fish (king mackerel). In spite of the fish being masala fried, you could specifically taste the fish.
Now you would be surprised to know why I said so. I have tried out many fish dishes where they just have a taste of masala, but this fish had a perfect blend of Indian spices on the fish and tasted yummy. The squid was delicious.
Another surprise was that we got 4 slices of beautiful fish and it just cost us Rs.400, whereas it would cost you around Rs.1000+ in Mumbai.
The taste of the food is really awesome, and you should definitely try out their seafood menu.
The service staff were really nice and interactive. I enjoyed spending time at this restaurant.

description:
**Valley View Restaurant: An Authentic Goan Seafood Experience**

Nestled conveniently close to the highway in Goa, Valley View Restaurant boasts a commendable rating of 3.9 from a solid community of 768 diners. Known primarily for its exquisite seafood offerings, including the highly recommended "kingfish thali" and "chonak thali," this dining establishment enjoys a reputation that aligns nicely with the recurring themes found in customer reviews. Alongside seafood, guests often mention ample "parking" and occasionally note aspects of "behaviour" relating to the service.

**Ambiance & Design**

The restaurant greets visitors with a warm and inviting atmosphere, featuring a blend of outdoor seating surrounded by lush greenery, which creates a peaceful dining experience. The dÃ©cor reflects a rustic charm, with wooden furnishings and natural elements that enhance the serene ambiance, making it an ideal spot for families or friends wishing to unwind. The photos taken by patrons reveal bright and spacious interiors, as well as well-maintained outdoor areas that invite diners to relish their meals while immersed in nature. While the setting exudes tranquility, itâ€™s worth noting that accessibility might be a concern for older guests due to the multiple steps leading up to the restaurantâ€™s entrance.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

Valley View's menu shines with its signature seafood dishes, particularly the kingfish thali and chonak thali, praised for their generous portions and flavorful preparations. One customer noted the satisfying size of the fish served, commenting on the juice and spice profile that elevated the dining experience. With an array of offerings, from butter chicken and parathas to unique local dishes like sol kadi and prawn curry, there is something to suit everyone's palate. While one guest expressed disappointment over the freshness of some elements in the thali, others were delighted by the quality and taste of the seafood, highlighting the restaurantâ€™s ability to serve flavors that can compete with pricier establishments in metropolitan areas.

**Customer Experience & Service**

Customer experiences at Valley View appear to be a mixed bag. On one hand, many reviewers appreciated the friendly demeanor of some staff members, noting how they were quick to address mistakes in ordersâ€”an essential trait in the often chaotic restaurant vibe. On the other hand, several diners reported issues with service efficiency, often citing slow delivery times and occasional internal communication mishaps. Despite these hiccups, enthusiasm for the food consistently shines through, suggesting that the culinary offerings make up for any service shortcomings. Reservations are not explicitly mentioned, though the open and spacious layout may allow for reasonable walk-in traffic.

**Popularity & Reviews**

The buzz surrounding Valley View is largely centered on its seafood, with many patrons returning to enjoy shared meals with friends and family against the backdrop of Goa's natural beauty. Customers consistently emphasize the restaurant's view and accessibility from the highway, making it a convenient stop for both locals and tourists. While ratings for ambiance and hygiene show room for improvementâ€”scoring only 3 starsâ€”the food itself commands an impressive 4-star rating among diners. With social media highlighting various dishes and inviting scenery, Valley View maintains a steady flow of visitors eager to explore its culinary charms.

**Utilizing Visual Content**

The array of customer-provided photos vividly captures the restaurant's inviting atmosphere and delectable dishes. One striking image showcases a beautifully presented kingfish thali, overflowing with vibrant colors from fresh ingredients, amidst a serene outdoor setting that invites leisurely dining. Other photographs highlight the spaciousness of the restaurant, emphasizing the inviting greenery that surrounds this picturesque spot.

In conclusion, Valley View Restaurant provides a delightful seafood experience infused with the charm of Goa. While some refinements in service efficiency could enhance overall enjoyment, the dedication to quality food makes it a worthwhile dining destination for anyone seeking to indulge in Goan flavors while basking in a nature-filled ambiance.
